  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p local-id=\"d7b22b8019b8\">Twilio is a third-party service that users can register for, to deliver SMS messages via a purchased phone number. This is a required service to send SMS messages outside of the United States and Canada.</p><p local-id=\"311cbb112b32\">In the US and Canada, RepairQ can send SMS messages for free using the customer's phone number and assigning the carrier's email gateway to their <a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1933312070/Managing+Customer+Profiles\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1933312070\" data-linked-resource-version=\"6\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Customer Profile</a>.</p><p local-id=\"73243a5bdcf4\">You must have a Twilio account and an SMS-capable phone number to enable the integration with RepairQ. If you need to sign up for a Twilio account, click <a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://www.twilio.com/try-twilio\" rel=\"nofollow\"><strong>here</strong></a><strong>.</strong></p><div class=\"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-note\"><span class=\"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-warning confluence-information-macro-icon\"></span><div class=\"confluence-information-macro-body\"><p local-id=\"c5b74c3a12a2\">Automated Notifications are intended for transactional and relationship messaging (ticket updates, pickup notifications, internal alerts), not for marketing or promotional content. </p><p local-id=\"2b4020ad51f7\">For details and regulatory context, see <a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1933246478/Getting+Started+with+Automated+Notifications\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1933246478\" data-linked-resource-version=\"13\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Getting Started with Automated Notifications</a> </p></div></div><h3 local-id=\"c54501bae58c\" id=\"Integrations:Twilio-AdditionalResources\">Additional Resources</h3><ul local-id=\"94c1f1010f47\"><li local-id=\"5ad45cae053c\"><p local-id=\"14d3f4bdab8c\"><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1933246465/Automated+Notification+Resources\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1933246465\" data-linked-resource-version=\"13\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Automated Notification Resources</a></p></li><li local-id=\"ed1e9b5eb99c\"><p local-id=\"2935f7a60371\"><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1933803736/Send+an+SMS+Ticket+Status+Notification\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1933803736\" data-linked-resource-version=\"11\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Sending an SMS Notification to a Customer</a></p></li><li local-id=\"bdb7d68a03b9\"><p local-id=\"b25ebe1ba644\"><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1933312070/Managing+Customer+Profiles\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1933312070\" data-linked-resource-version=\"6\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Managing Customer Profiles</a></p></li><li local-id=\"13e3f834db9a\"><p local-id=\"f915cf240513\"><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/servicedesk/customer/portal/9/article/1932361859\" rel=\"nofollow\">Integration Setup: Revv/Rallio</a></p></li></ul><hr local-id=\"416fd0c7f151\"/><h2 local-id=\"fb0b80025f7b\" id=\"Integrations:Twilio-SMSNotificationsinRepairQ\">SMS Notifications in RepairQ</h2><p local-id=\"976e7ad355e9\">Certain requirements will allow for outgoing communications to the customer:</p><ul local-id=\"3ab00158f6a7\"><li local-id=\"28ddde13d27e\"><p local-id=\"e689cbf3b7f4\">To send a notification, the ticket has to have a Customer Profile attached.</p></li><li local-id=\"a387c15c7789\"><p local-id=\"10931c964193\">The <a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1933312070/Managing+Customer+Profiles\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1933312070\" data-linked-resource-version=\"6\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Customer Profile</a> must have a phone number in the <strong>SMS Phone</strong> field.</p><ul local-id=\"74ceaf1beadd\"><li local-id=\"87c2ce7336c6\"><p local-id=\"3d100c81f9d3\">An accurate carrier must be selected in the <strong>SMS Carrier</strong> field. If using Twilio, you can choose N/A as the carrier. <strong>Do not leave this field blank</strong>.</p></li><li local-id=\"8abd0fa6eae5\"><p local-id=\"742de37f41ae\">The <strong>Receive Notifications</strong> fields must be set to <strong>Yes</strong>.</p></li><li local-id=\"3999a8cce115\"><p local-id=\"654c4c4e3f31\">The <strong>Receive SMS Messages</strong> <strong>checkbox must be selected</strong>.</p></li></ul></li></ul><p local-id=\"4f50401f09d4\">For additional instructions on how to set up notifications and send them to the customer, see our Knowledge Base articles <a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1933803736/Send+an+SMS+Ticket+Status+Notification\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1933803736\" data-linked-resource-version=\"11\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Sending an SMS Notification to a Customer</a> and <a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1933246465/Automated+Notification+Resources\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1933246465\" data-linked-resource-version=\"13\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Automated Notifications</a>.</p><hr local-id=\"47cc6483b771\"/><h2 local-id=\"67f2eac5e402\" id=\"Integrations:Twilio-TwilioAccountSetupandCredentials\">Twilio Account Setup and Credentials</h2><p local-id=\"f8b4ecbd8b0f\">If you haven't yet, <a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://www.twilio.com/try-twilio\" rel=\"nofollow\"><strong>sign up for Twilio</strong></a>. Make sure to pick a phone number with SMS capabilities by checking the SMS box before clicking Search to see a good list of compatible numbers. Once you have set up your Twilio account, log in. RepairQ requires three credentials from your Twilio account for integration:</p><ul local-id=\"c0ac70d0df84\"><li local-id=\"3d44a80acf66\"><p local-id=\"ab4efb7afa3f\"><strong>Your Twilio Account SID</strong></p></li><li local-id=\"5c2f01c42d9e\"><p local-id=\"d90f4686410d\"><strong>Your Twilio account Auto Token</strong></p></li><li local-id=\"e4324d105119\"><p local-id=\"75383abd27c5\"><strong>Your Twilio number</strong></p></li></ul><p local-id=\"2eaf607aa4cd\">Your Account SID and Auth Token can be found by clicking <strong>Show API Credentials</strong>. Your Twilio number can be found by clicking <strong>Get your Twilio number</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" width=\"571\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933803609/Twilio%201.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" width=\"571\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933803609/Twilio%202.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" width=\"574\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933803609/Twilio%204.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"340\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933803609/Twilio%203.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 local-id=\"74cb416048c7\" id=\"Integrations:Twilio-TwilioIntegrationinRepairQ\">Twilio Integration in RepairQ</h2><p local-id=\"e6d0cadf0bcb\">On the Navigation Bar, go to <strong>Settings</strong> \u2192 <strong>Company</strong> <strong>Settings</strong>. On the Settings Overview page, click <strong>Integrations</strong>.</p><p local-id=\"0bedd61925ba\"><strong>Note</strong>: If you have multiple locations that will use separate accounts, this information can also be entered at the Location level by navigating to <strong>Settings </strong>\u2192 <strong>Location Settings</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933803609/Twilio%205.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" width=\"878\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933803609/Twilio%206.png?api=v2\"></span><p local-id=\"760a7504a1c4\" /><p local-id=\"f336b74d4612\">On the Integrations page, select Twilio from the Available Integrations section. Next, enter your credentials from your Twilio account. Make sure that the <strong>checkbox for Enable Tw</strong>i<strong>lio is selected</strong>. Once you are finished entering your credentials, click <strong>Save Twilio Settings</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" width=\"633\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933803609/Twilio%207.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" width=\"633\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933803609/Twilio%209.png?api=v2\"></span><p local-id=\"2e3dde62210e\" /><p local-id=\"e8166dc4fb6c\" /><p local-id=\"3bde3084e4d6\">START 1.21.X</p>",
